org.jlab.coda.emu.support.transport

Interface DataChannel

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CODAStateMachine, StatedObject
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DataChannelAdapter, DataChannelImplCmsg, DataChannelImplEmu, DataChannelImplEt, DataChannelImplFifo, DataChannelImplFile

    public interface DataChannel
extends CODAStateMachine, StatedObject
    This interface defines an object that can send and receive data. It refers to a single, particular connection (eg. a single socket or cMsg connection object).
    Author:
    heyes, timmer Created on Sep 12, 2008

      • getID

        int getID()
        Get the CODA ID number of the CODA component connected to this data channel. In event building, this is used, for example, to check the ROC id of incoming event which allows consistency checking.
        Returns:
        the CODA ID number the CODA component connected to this data channel.

      • getRecordId

        int getRecordId()
        Get the record ID number of the latest event through this channel. In CODA event building this is used, for example, to track the record ids for input events which allows consistency checks of incoming data.
        Returns:
        the record ID number of the latest event through channel.

      • getOutputLevel

        int getOutputLevel()
        Get the relative fill level (0-100) of all the rings of this output channel. Module calls this to report its output channels' levels. (Input levels are associated directly with the module).
        Returns:
        relative fill level (0-100) of all the rings together.

      • setDestinationIpList

        void setDestinationIpList(java.lang.String[] ipList)
        Set the output channel's list of possible destination IP addresses of emu TCP server when using emu sockets to communicate.
        Parameters:
        ipList - list of possible destination IP addresses if connecting to server.

      • setDestinationBaList

        void setDestinationBaList(java.lang.String[] baList)
        Set the output channel's list of destination broadcast addresses of emu TCP server when using emu sockets to communicate - each corresponding to the same element of the IpList.
        Parameters:
        baList - list of destination broadcast addresses each corresponding to the same element of the IpList.

      • getPrescale

        int getPrescale()
        Get the prescale value associated with this channel. Defaults to 1. Used only for ET output of ER.
        Returns:
        prescale value associated with this channel.

      • regulateOutputBufferRate

        void regulateOutputBufferRate(int eventsPerBuffer,
                              double buffersPerSec)
        Turn on regulation of the flow of data through an output channel. Currently this is implemented only for the emu socket channel - for testing purposes. It sets the rate of output buffers (typically 4MB each) and specifies the number of ROC (entangled) events per buffer.
        Parameters:
        eventsPerBuffer - events per output 4 MB buffer.
        buffersPerSec - desired number of buffers to be sent per second.
